description: AIC Mines Limited explores for and develops gold and copper deposits in Australia. It holds a 100% interest in the Marymia project comprising an area of approximately 3,600 square kilometers located in the Eastern Gascoyne region of Western Australia; the Eloise copper mine located in North Queensland; and 65% interest in the Lamil project that covers an area of 1,200 square kilometers located in the Paterson Province of Western Australia. The company has also applied for two large exploration licenses located in the Delamerian Orogen in western New South Wales. AIC Mines Limited was incorporated in 1993 and is based in Subiaco, Australia.
ceo: Mr. Aaron Mark Colleran B.Com., B.E., M.A.I.C.D., MAICD, BEng Geology, BCo
